    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, p 953.) While benzodiazepines are generally recognized to be extremely safe medications, when taken in an overdose in combination with alcohol they can be particularly dangerous. Alcohol has an additive effect to the CNS and respiratory depressant effects of benzodiazepines, because it increases the binding affinity of benzodiazepines to the benzodiazepine-binding site.",
