    "source": "pretest",
    "difficulty": 2,
    "vignette": "A 27-year-old woman undergoes a large bilateral resection of the medial temporal lobes in an effort to stop her increasingly severe seizures. Although the seizures improved, she was found to have severe anterograde amnesia. For example, she was able to immediately repeat a phone number given to her during examination, but could not remember the examiner who gave her the number if the examiner left the room and came back several minutes later. Which of the following area of the brain 1s responsible for consolidation of long-term memories?",
