    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, p 535.) Dreaming is the main characteristic of REM sleep. The EEG shows characteristic low-voltage waves that are random, fast, and sawtoothed. Active eye movements are attributed to the individual’s “watching” his or her dreams. A lack of muscle tone during REM sleep prevents the individual from acting out his or her dreams. REM sleep 1s also characterized by increased heart rate and blood pressure and penile or clitoral nocturnal erections.",
