    "correct": "B",
    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, p 995.) Monoamine oxidases (including tranylcypromine) inactivate biogenic amines such as norepinephrine, serotonin, dopamine, and tyramine through oxidative deamination. The MAOIs block this inactivation, thereby increasing the availability of these neurotransmitters for synaptic release. However MAOIs also inactivate GI metabolism of dietary tyramine, thus allowing unaltered tyramine into the circulation. This amino acid has a potent pressor effect.",
