    "vignette": "A 22-year-old woman is brought to the emergency room by her friends after she took some pills at a party and subsequently developed physical symptoms including her neck twisting painfully, and her eyes involuntarily rolling upward. The patient responds immediately to 50 mg of diphenhydramine intramuscularly with rapid resolution of all physical symptoms. Which of the following substances is most likely to have caused these symptoms?",
