    "vignette": "A 71-year-old man has been treated by a neurologist for Parkinson disease for the past 2 years. One week after his last visit, he called his neurologist, reporting that he suddenly began seeing little people walking all over his furniture. The patient had never previously reported symptoms as described. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in the management of this patient?",
