    "vignette": "A 35-year-old man presents to his physician with a slowly developing difficulty of movement and thinking. The patient tells the physician that his father had similar problems. His wife notes that the patient appears depressed and apathetic. On examination, the patient has involuntary choreiform movements of his face, hands, and shoulders. Which of the following areas of the brain 1s likely to show atrophy with this disease?",
