    "vignette": "A 13-year-old boy is brought to the emergency room by his parents after he set fire to their home. He has been seen in the emergency room on multiple occasions for a variety of symptoms, including suicidality, homicidality, uncontrollable tantrums, and pica. Of those symptoms, which is most commonly seen in adolescents when seen by psychiatrists in the emergency room?",
