    "correct": "E",
    "explanation_text": "(Fletcher, Fletcher, and Fletcher, p 174.) Sensitivity 1s defined as the number of true positives divided by the sum of the number of true positives and false negatives. (a/atc in the table below) It is the proportion of patients with the condition 1n question that the test can detect. Thus, the sensitivity in this case is calculated by 33/38=0.87. Test positive Test negative Totals Gold standard disease present True positives (TP) a False negatives (FN) c Total diseased atc Gold standard disease absent False positives (FP) b True negatives (TN) d Total normal b+d Total number of patients Who test positive a+b Who test negative c+d Total number of patients in table a+tb+c+d",
