    "explanation_text": "(Fletcher, Fletcher, and Fletcher, p 145.) The positive predictive value (PPV) of a diagnostic test is calculated by the formula PPV = a/at+b, which in this case 1s 33/83. The PPV is the percentage of patients who have the disease and have a positive test, divided by the percentage of the total number of patients who test positive. Thought of another way, it 1s the percentage of patients who actually have the disease who test positive for the disease.",
