    "id": "PT-EVAL-035",
    "domain": "evaluation",
    "source": "pretest",
    "difficulty": 2,
    "vignette": "An 18-year-old man is brought to the emergency room by the police after he is found walking along the edge of a high building. In the emergency room, he mumbles to himself and appears to be responding to internal stimuli. When asked open-ended questions, he suddenly stops his answer in the middle of a sentence, as if he has forgotten what to say. Which of the following symptoms best describes this last behavior?",
