    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, p 203.) Depersonalization refers to feeling that one 1s falling apart or not one’s self, that one’s self is unreal or detached. Derealization is the subjective sense that the environment is strange or unreal, as if reality had been changed. Perception 1s a physical sensation given a meaning or the integration of sensory stimuli to form an image or impression; in dulled perception, this capacity is diminished. Retardation of thought refers to the slowing of thought processes that may be seen in major depression. Response time to questions may be increased.",
