    "correct": "A",
    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, p 779.) The use of a benzodiazepine and a high-potency antipsychotic has several advantages. While the antipsychotic treats the psychosis without a lot of anticholinergic side effects, the benzodiazepine reduces the amount of antipsychotic needed and protects the patient against dystonic reactions. Clozapine or fluphenazine decanoate would never be given in an acute setting.",
