    "correct": "E",
    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, pp 356, 360.) This patient 1s presenting with a major depressive disorder with psychotic features. For over 2 weeks (the minimum for the diagnosis), the patient has been complaining of anhedonia, crying, anergia, decreased concentration, 10 Ib weight loss, and insomnia with early morning awakening. She also has somatic delusions that are mood congruent and an auditory hallucination. The presence of psychotic phenomena that follow a clear mood disorder picture makes the diagnosis of major depressive disorder with psychotic features the most likely.",
    "explanations": null,
