    "correct": "B",
    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, pp 972-980.) There 1s strong evidence that without continuous treatment, virtually all schizophrenic patients relapse within 12 to 24 months. Both haloperidol and fluphenazine are available in long-acting forms. Injectable depot medications such as these are effective in decreasing the rate of relapse in patients who are not adherentwith oral medication.",
