    "vignette": "A 28-year-old woman is brought to see a psychiatrist by her mother. The patient insists that nothing is wrong with her, but the mother notes that the patient has been slowly but progressively isolating herself from everyone. She now rarely leaves the house. The mother says she can hear the patient talking to “people who aren’t there” while she’s in her room. On examination, the patient 1s noted to have auditory hallucinations and the delusional belief that her mother is going to kick her out of the house so that it can be turned into a theme park. Which of the following 1s the lifetime prevalence for this disorder?",
