    "correct": "D",
    "explanation_text": "(Kaplan and Sadock, p 318.) Factors predicting a good outcome in schizophrenia include age at onset of 20 to 25, married status, and a good premorbid social and/or work history. Other adverse social factors are missing, and the family history is one of affective disorder, not schizophrenia. In addition, precipitating factors are usually present, and the onset of the disease is rapid, not insidious, 1n patients with good-outcome schizophrenia.",
