    "domain": "psychosis",
    "source": "pretest",
    "difficulty": 2,
    "vignette": "A 22-year-old man 1s brought to the emergency room after he became exceedingly anxious in his college dormitory room, stating that he was sure the college administration was sending a “hit squad” to kill him. He also notes that he can see “visions” of men dressed in black who are carrying guns and stalking him. His thought process is relatively intact, without thought blocking or loose associations. His urine toxicology screen is positive for one of the following drugs. Which drug 1s the most likely cause of these symptoms?",
